]]), colors: {{color box|#FF0000}} [[Red]] and {{color box|#FFCC00}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]]\n*[[Phi Sigma Iota]], \u03a6\u03a3\u0399 ([[modern foreign languages]], [[Classics]], [[linguistics]], [[philology]], [[comparative literature]], [[bilingual education]], [[second language acquisition]]), colors: {{color box|#7851A9}} [[Royal Purple|Purple]] and {{color box|#FFFFFF}} [[White]]\n\n=====Fine arts=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\n*[[Alpha Psi Omega]], \u0391\u03a8\u03a9 ([[theatre]])\n*[[Kappa Pi]], \u039a\u03a0 ([[art]])\n*[[Kappa Kappa Psi]], \u039a\u039a\u03a8 (music - band)\n*[[Mu Beta Psi]], \u039c\u0392\u03a8 (music)\n*[[Pi Kappa Lambda]], \u03a0\u039a\u039b ([[Music]])\n*[[Pi Nu Epsilon]], \u03a0\u039d\u0395 ([[music]])\n*[[Tau Beta Sigma]], \u03a4\u0392\u03a3 ([[music]] - band)\n*[[Theta Alpha Phi]], \u0398\u0391\u03a6 ([[Theatre]])\n\n=====Business=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\n*[[Alpha Iota Delta]], \u0391\u0399\u0394 ([[decision sciences]])\n*[[Alpha Mu Alpha]], AMA ([[marketing]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ama.org/students/Pages/Alpha-Mu-Alpha.aspx|title=Alpha Mu Alpha|website=www.ama.org|access-date=2015-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150423062125/https://www.ama.org/students/Pages/Alpha-Mu-Alpha.aspx|archive-date=2015-04-23|url-status=live}}</ref> color: {{color box|Red}} [[Red]]\n*[[Beta Alpha Psi]], \u0392\u0391\u03a8 ([[accounting]])\n*[[Beta Gamma Sigma]], \u0392\u0393\u03a3 ([[AACSB]] accredited [[business]] programs), colors: {{color box|#FFD700}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]] and {{color box|#0F4D92}} [[Yale Blue]] \n*[[Delta Mu Delta]], \u0394\u039c\u0394 ([[ACBSP]] accredited [[business]] programs)\n*[[Mu Kappa Tau]], \u039c\u039a\u03a4 ([[marketing]])\n*[[Omega Rho]], \u03a9\u03a1 ([[operations research]], [[management science]])\n*[[Omicron Delta Epsilon]], \u039f\u0394\u0395 ([[economics]]), colors: {{color box|#0000FF}} [[