ates Air Force]] [[cadet]]s)\n*[[Pershing Rifles]] ([[United States armed forces]])\n*[[Scabbard and Blade]] ([[Reserve Officers' Training Corps|ROTC]] [[cadet]]s and [[Midshipman|midshipmen]])\n\n=====Other=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\nAlpha Mu, AM, (Agricultural Systems Management)\n*[[Beta Phi Mu]], \u0392\u03a6\u039c ([[library science]]/[[information science]]/[[information technology]])\n*[[Chi Epsilon Pi]], \u03a7\u0395\u03a0 ([[meteorology]])\n*[[Chi Sigma Iota]], \u03a7\u03a3\u0399 ([[counseling]])\n*[[Epsilon Pi Tau]], \u0395\u03a0\u03a4 ([[technology]])\n*[[Epsilon Tau Pi]], \u0395\u03a4\u03a0 ([[Eagle Scout (Boy Scouts of America)|Eagle Scouts]])\n*[[Gamma Nu Eta]], \u0393\u039d\u0397 (information technology)\n*[[Nu Rho Psi]], \u039d\u03a1\u03a8 ([[neuroscience]])\n*[[Order of the Sword & Shield]], \u039f\u03a3\u03a3 ([[homeland security]], [[intelligence]], emergency management, and all protective studies)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securityhonorsociety.org/|title=Order of the Sword & Shield|website=Order of the Sword & Shield National Honor Society|access-date=2015-10-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151021015836/http://www.securityhonorsociety.org/|archive-date=2015-10-21|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Phi Tau Sigma]], \u03a6\u03a4\u03a3 (Food Science and Technology)\n*[[Phi Upsilon Omicron]], \u03a6\u03a5\u039f ([[Family and consumer science]]), colors: {{color box|#8F00FF}} [[Violet (color)|Violet]], {{color box|#FFD700}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]] and {{color box|#FFFDD0}} [[Cream (colour)|Cream]] \n*[[Pi Alpha Alpha]], \u03a0\u0391\u0391 ([[public administration]])\n*[[Pi Epsilon]], \u03a0\u0395 ([[environmental sciences]])\n*[[Pi Theta Epsilon]], \u03a0\u0398\u0395 ([[occupational therapy]])\n*[[Sigma Gamma Epsilon]], \u03a3\u0393\u0395 ([[geology]]/[[Earth sciences]])\n*[[Sigma Iota Rho]], \u03a3\u0399\u03a1 ([[international relations]])\n*[[Sigma Lambda Alpha (honor society)|Sigma Lambda Alpha]], \u03a3\u039b\u0391 ([[landscape architecture]]), colors: {{color box|#FFD700}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]] and {{color box|#008000}} [[Green]]\n*[[Sigma Lambda Chi]], \u03a3\u039b\u03a7 ([[construction management]] technology)\n*Sigma Phi Omega, \u03a3\u03a6\u03a9, ([[Gerontology]])<ref>[https://www.sigmaphiomega.org/ \u03a3\u03a6\u03a9's national website] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013133846/https://www.sigmaphiomega.org/ |date=2016-10-13 }}, accessed 12 Oct 2016. Not to be confused with the Asian-interest sorority of the same name.</ref>\n*[[Theta Alpha Kappa]], \u0398\u0391\u039a, (Religious Studies/theology)\n*[[Xi Sigma Pi]], \u039e\u03a3\u03a0 ([[forestry]]), colors: {{color box|#008000}} [[Green]] and {{color box|#BEBEBE}} [[Grey|Gray]]\n\n==== Independent societies ====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\nSome universities have their own independent, open honor societies, which are not affiliated with any national or international organization. Such organizations typically recognize students who have succeeded academically irrespective of their field of study. These include:\n\n*Activities Honorary Society at [[University of Illinois at Chicago]]\n*[[Aquinas Honor Society]] at [[University of St. Thomas (Houston)|University of St. Thomas]]\n*Bisonhead at the [[University at Buffalo, The State University of New York]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Bison Head at the University of Buffalo|url=http://library.buffalo.edu/archives/student-life/campus/activities.htm|publisher=University at Buffalo Libraries|accessdate=20 February 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912204613/http://library.buffalo.edu/archives/student-life/campus/activities.htm|archive-date=2014-09-12|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Burning Spear Society]] at [[Florida State University]]\n*[[Cap and Skull]] at [[Rutgers University]]\n*[[FHC Society]] at [[The College of William & Mary]]\n*[[Florida Blue Key]] at [[University of 