e]], [[law]])\n\n=====Journalism and communications=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\n*[[Kappa Tau Alpha]], \u039a\u03a4\u0391 ([[journalism]]/[[mass communication]]), colors: {{color box|#ADD8E6}} [[Blue|Light blue]] and {{color box|#FFD700}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]] \n*[[Lambda Pi Eta]], \u039b\u03a0\u0397 ([[communication]])\n*[[Society for Collegiate Journalists]], (SCJ) ([[journalism]])\n\n=====Languages=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\n*[[Alpha Mu Gamma]], \u0391\u039c\u0393 ([[foreign languages]]), color: {{color box|#FFCC00}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]]\n*[[German National Honor Society|Delta Phi Alpha]], \u0394\u03a6\u0391 - ([[German language|German]]), colors: {{color box|#000000}} [[Black]], {{color box|#FF0000}} [[Red]] and {{color box|#FFCC00}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]]\n*[[Pi Delta Phi]], \u03a0\u0394\u03a6 ([[French language|French]]), colors: {{color box|#0000FF}} [[Blue]], {{color box|#FFFFFF}} [[White]] and {{color box|#FF0000}} [[Red]]\n*[[Sigma Delta Pi]], \u03a3\u0394\u03a0 ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]), colors: {{color box|#FF0000}} [[Red]] and {{color box|#FFCC00}} [[Gold (color)|Gold]]\n*[[Phi Sigma Iota]], \u03a6\u03a3\u0399 ([[modern foreign languages]], [[Classics]], [[linguistics]], [[philology]], [[comparative literature]], [[bilingual education]], [[second language acquisition]], colors: {{color box|#7851A9}} [[Royal Purple|Purple]] and {{color box|#FFFFFF}} [[White]]\n\n=====Fine arts=====\n<!--Editors: to add color swatches, see the Talk page for instructions.-->\n*[[Alpha Psi Omega]], \u0391\u03a8\u03a9 ([[theatre]])\n*[[Kappa Pi]], \u039a\u03a0 ([[art]])\n*[[Kappa Kappa Psi]], \u039a\u039a\u03a8 (music - band)\n*[[Mu Beta Psi]], \u039c\u0392\u03a8 (music)\n*[[Pi Kappa Lambda]], \u03a0\u039a\u039b ([[Music]])\n*[[Pi Nu Epsilon]], \u03a0\u039d\u0395 ([[music]])\n*[[Tau Beta Sigma]], \u03a4\u0392\u03a3 ([[music]]